2022 Recap A trip into healing and self love and a return to bad bitchery 😌

I remain a perpetual student of life and am so blessed to have amazing support from friends family and YOU! With everything we push through we get better stronger and wiser. This Moon-month takes its name not from blood sacrifices, but from the old custom of killing and salting down the livestock before the winter months made it impossible to feed them. Today we still subconsciously begin making preparations for the coming winter during this time. We check the antifreeze and tires for the car, gather up the garden hoses, and make plans to winterize any drafty spots around doors and windows in the house.
